WEBVTT

01:38.240 --> 01:40.520
EPISODE 9

01:43.120 --> 01:47.160
Uncle, Auntie, I'm sorry.

01:48.720 --> 01:49.600
I was the one driving.

01:51.200 --> 01:55.080
When the accident happened,
Nai pushed me out of harm's way.

01:55.760 --> 01:57.160
Otherwise, I'd be the one lying here.

01:57.640 --> 02:00.520
Kid, don't be so hard on yourself.

02:00.920 --> 02:02.760
Accidents can't be predicted.

02:04.080 --> 02:07.560
Thankfully, he's awake now. Good fortune
comes after surviving a disaster.

02:08.479 --> 02:09.479
That's right.

02:10.720 --> 02:12.400
I should call our relatives.

02:12.480 --> 02:16.680
- They're all waiting for the news.
- Hurry. Lie still and don't move.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
Nai, are you sure you're okay?

02:24.080 --> 02:26.680
Are you dizzy? Are you in pain at all?

02:27.400 --> 02:30.520
Here, look at me...

02:31.960 --> 02:34.640
What's one plus one?

02:35.920 --> 02:36.800
One.

02:39.200 --> 02:43.040
- No! I have to find the doctor!
- Enough! Calm down.

02:43.120 --> 02:45.200
It's obvious Nai is fine now.

02:45.360 --> 02:47.720
He knows you're not worth two cents.

02:51.480 --> 02:53.680
- What time is it?
- Five in the afternoon.

02:54.000 --> 02:56.960
You should log in and inform Weiwei.

02:58.640 --> 03:01.680
- Mrs. Nai?
- Wait, given the circumstances...

03:01.760 --> 03:03.960
Why are you still thinking about the game?

03:04.960 --> 03:06.160
Mrs. Nai?

03:08.640 --> 03:10.840
Please don't tell me,
she waited for you all night...

03:14.520 --> 03:15.520
Mrs. Nai?

03:19.320 --> 03:20.720
The doctor's here...

03:20.800 --> 03:21.760
Doctor.

03:22.800 --> 03:25.200
Please check if there'll be aftereffects
for my classmate!

03:35.880 --> 03:39.600
Xiao Nai's roommates mentioned "Mrs. Nai."
Is our son seeing someone?

03:40.560 --> 03:41.800
Not likely.

03:42.360 --> 03:44.360
Xiao Nai's got a quirky temper.

03:44.440 --> 03:47.720
I've never seen him be close with a girl.

03:47.800 --> 03:49.720
How would he get a partner so soon?

03:50.160 --> 03:54.440
- He'll be at least 40 when he marries.
- Why would you say that about our son?

03:54.920 --> 03:57.240
Although I agree with you,

03:57.320 --> 04:00.160
but his roommates call him "Nai,"

04:00.440 --> 04:02.280
what else would "Mrs. Nai" mean?

04:03.880 --> 04:06.720
It's probably a handle in gaming.

04:07.840 --> 04:09.080
Kids these days

04:09.160 --> 04:11.600
have all sorts of weird names online.

04:12.840 --> 04:15.240
The other day,
our literature professor told me,

04:15.320 --> 04:17.800
writers these days have crazy names.

04:18.399 --> 04:23.320
There's a writer named
"Three Spoons of Sugar," of all things.

04:23.400 --> 04:28.600
If "Three Spoons of Sugar" is acceptable,
why wouldn't "Mrs. Nai" be?

04:29.240 --> 04:34.520
So, "Mrs. Nai" is probably just
a funny nickname.

04:35.480 --> 04:36.600
That makes sense.

04:37.240 --> 04:41.840
Don't read too much into it.
We won't get a daughter-in-law so soon!

04:42.040 --> 04:46.960
Order a half-month worth of fish head soup
for him. That's good for concussion.

04:47.040 --> 04:47.880
Okay.

04:54.520 --> 04:55.920
This restaurant is near the hospital.

04:56.000 --> 04:58.360
Do you know what's good
for a concussion patient?

04:58.440 --> 05:01.600
Fish head soup is probably good for that.

05:01.680 --> 05:04.160
- Great. I'll take one.
- Nice.

05:04.560 --> 05:05.920
Then something light.

05:07.240 --> 05:10.280
Mushrooms with veggies
and a bowl of rice.

05:10.520 --> 05:13.280
Wait, let's get him
a stir-fried pork liver.

05:13.360 --> 05:15.720
- Stir-fried pork liver.
- Yes, that'll do.

05:16.480 --> 05:18.440
Just one bowl of rice?

05:19.040 --> 05:22.000
Those are to go, for here...

05:24.320 --> 05:29.400
A stir-fried eggs with tomato
and cucumber salad. Thanks.

05:31.320 --> 05:32.160
That's it?

05:36.240 --> 05:37.640
We're eating all vegetarian?

05:39.040 --> 05:40.280
I don't have any money.

05:43.200 --> 05:45.080
Nai's family may not blame me,

05:45.440 --> 05:46.800
but I have to pay for his medical bill.

05:47.160 --> 05:50.080
I'm sure health insurance will cover some?

05:50.520 --> 05:52.360
Yes... It'll cover it.

05:52.800 --> 05:53.840
Really?

05:54.680 --> 05:56.160
An order of sweet-and-sour pork.

05:56.480 --> 05:58.440
- Okay.
- Thanks.

06:15.760 --> 06:18.120
Hou, Mei,

06:19.400 --> 06:20.480
I only say this to you.

06:24.040 --> 06:28.920
From now on, I, Yu Banshan,

06:30.680 --> 06:32.720
will always be indebted to Nai,
even in death.

06:32.800 --> 06:33.920
I'm his for life.

06:35.360 --> 06:36.640
Why are you saying this out of the blue?

06:39.600 --> 06:41.920
You haven't had that kind of
near-death experience.

06:46.440 --> 06:48.720
The moment our car hit the truck,

06:50.800 --> 06:53.040
do you know what Nai's
instinctive reaction was?

06:55.360 --> 06:58.680
It was to push me out of harm's way,
then grab the steering wheel.

07:08.040 --> 07:12.160
I'm Yu Banshan. My life
isn't nearly as valuable as Nai's life!

07:14.160 --> 07:17.840
Why would he risk his life to save mine?

07:19.360 --> 07:23.280
I don't know if you've thought about it,
but I have.

07:24.200 --> 07:25.040
Nai...

07:27.400 --> 07:30.040
He's amazing. He's the master.
He's number one.

07:31.480 --> 07:32.560
I'm no competition.

07:35.760 --> 07:37.560
I used to think it's unfair, too.

07:40.800 --> 07:43.640
Why not? Why am I
no competition against him?

07:46.200 --> 07:48.520
But the evidence is clear,
so I must be convinced.

07:51.320 --> 07:52.880
I'm simply not as good as him.

07:54.920 --> 07:56.680
I'm sure everyone thinks so.

08:02.440 --> 08:07.600
Only Nai doesn't think so.

08:09.680 --> 08:11.080
His behavior has told me,

08:12.680 --> 08:14.480
in his mind,

08:16.240 --> 08:17.280
me...

08:19.520 --> 08:22.520
me, Yu Banshan's life
is just as valuable as his.

08:33.640 --> 08:35.840
In the past few days,
when Nai was in a coma,

08:39.400 --> 08:41.760
I thought, what if we weren't so lucky?

08:43.640 --> 08:45.320
What if we hadn't smashed into a tree,

08:45.400 --> 08:48.080
and instead hit the truck head-on?

08:51.720 --> 08:53.240
What would've happened to Nai?

08:55.480 --> 08:56.320
Stop that nonsense.

08:56.400 --> 09:00.920
Such a young life would've vanished,
because of me.

09:01.680 --> 09:05.720
Nai only suffered minor injuries.
He'll be fine and discharged in two days.

09:06.120 --> 09:07.480
I can't stop thinking about it.

09:11.040 --> 09:12.840
Nai didn't think about it,
when he saved me.

09:12.920 --> 09:15.480
He didn't know that...
he wouldn't get hurt.

09:16.560 --> 09:18.240
Even if he's not hurt,

09:19.840 --> 09:21.640
I'm laying it all out here today.

09:25.040 --> 09:27.400
From now on, I'll do whatever
Xiao Nai tells me.

09:29.720 --> 09:34.160
Come hell or high water,
I won't even blink an eye.

09:35.640 --> 09:36.560
Well...

09:37.200 --> 09:39.000
Spit it out!

09:41.040 --> 09:44.800
Actually, I can totally relate
to what you're going through,

09:45.160 --> 09:46.760
but I have to tell you,

09:46.840 --> 09:51.000
there won't be hell or high water
in our lives with Nai.

09:51.360 --> 09:53.720
- We'll only enjoy the finest of life.
- Right...

09:53.800 --> 09:56.480
Also, you'd better get it in your head,

09:57.080 --> 09:58.720
if you want to be Nai's for life,

09:58.800 --> 10:01.320
you can only be a concubine,
since he's already got a wife.

10:05.680 --> 10:08.280
- I'm serious!
- Fine, I know you're serious.

10:08.360 --> 10:09.600
Let's go in.

10:09.680 --> 10:12.520
Nai survived the car accident,
but he might starve to death.

10:12.800 --> 10:15.160
Yes, let's go in quickly.
You've been crying all day.

10:15.240 --> 10:16.280
- Let's go.
- Come on.

10:16.840 --> 10:17.760
Hold on.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.240
Are my eyes red?

10:24.280 --> 10:25.560
I can't let him see me like this,

10:25.640 --> 10:27.360
or that shameless rascal will tease me.

10:27.920 --> 10:30.520
- Okay... Everything's fine now.
- Don't cry.

10:30.600 --> 10:32.040
Come on, let's go.

10:38.960 --> 10:44.560
What's this monster? So sick!
I'll send you back to hell!

10:44.640 --> 10:49.640
Ultimate...

10:50.600 --> 10:52.240
I can't get it to work.

10:52.920 --> 10:55.040
Forget it! My life's at risk.

10:57.640 --> 11:00.400
Oh, no! I can't get away!

11:00.840 --> 11:03.080
I'll have my heroine do you in!

11:03.840 --> 11:05.720
Ms. Weiwei, Mayday!

11:08.560 --> 11:09.840
Weiwei?

11:11.320 --> 11:13.760
How can you be that into
an instructional book?

11:13.840 --> 11:16.200
Come on! Help me destroy this monster.

11:19.440 --> 11:20.600
Come on...

11:24.400 --> 11:28.120
- Ms. Heroine, I beg of you!
- Let go.

11:42.800 --> 11:46.960
Bumptious little thing! I'll show you!

11:47.040 --> 11:50.160
You'll crawl away from me, from now on.

11:56.080 --> 11:58.200
Weiwei, off him with a slash.

11:59.080 --> 12:01.400
- Get lost. Don't get in the way.
- Got it.

12:12.520 --> 12:15.760
What's wrong, Weiwei? Are you ill?

12:26.240 --> 12:27.080
Erxi...

12:30.800 --> 12:34.120
Do you have a good friend in the game?

12:38.680 --> 12:40.160
Yes.

12:44.160 --> 12:45.120
Yes, I do.

12:46.920 --> 12:48.640
Have you thought about meeting him?

12:51.520 --> 12:55.000
No, what's the point in that?

12:57.720 --> 13:00.600
What if he suddenly disappears one day,

13:01.560 --> 13:03.440
or never come online anymore?

13:03.880 --> 13:08.040
Every day, the two of you
go to the instance dungeon together,

13:08.120 --> 13:10.160
and you spend a lot of time
with each other,

13:10.680 --> 13:12.120
but he simply vanishes,

13:13.480 --> 13:17.000
and you don't know who he is,
or where he is.

13:18.640 --> 13:23.280
Even if you see him in a crowd,
he's just a stranger.

13:25.720 --> 13:27.440
But, isn't gaming like that?

13:27.880 --> 13:31.400
Newcomers arrive every day,
and some others leave every day.

13:31.920 --> 13:36.400
I might have just started gaming,
but that seems to be normal?

13:41.440 --> 13:45.000
Yes, it's normal in gaming.

13:46.720 --> 13:48.440
I thought I got used to it.

13:52.320 --> 13:57.040
But why do I feel so panicky this time?

13:58.520 --> 14:01.200
What's the matter, Weiwei?

14:02.640 --> 14:04.120
I'm going to study now.

14:19.320 --> 14:22.760
There are so many departures
without goodbyes in gaming.

14:23.520 --> 14:27.240
Would Naihe disappear like that, too?

14:28.480 --> 14:30.160
In the long, long days to come,

14:30.520 --> 14:32.520
would this video be the only evidence

14:32.800 --> 14:35.520
of me ever knowing Naihe?

14:36.680 --> 14:40.360
But, maybe Naihe was simply
held up somewhere?

14:40.840 --> 14:42.960
Why am I making a big deal out of it?

14:44.080 --> 14:46.280
As for whether Naihe has vanished,

14:46.560 --> 14:48.920
I only have to log on to find out.

14:49.720 --> 14:51.600
Why am I afraid to log on?

15:12.760 --> 15:15.720
Oh, no... I'm being sentimental.

15:16.320 --> 15:19.200
Oh, no, I seem to be...

15:21.160 --> 15:23.720
I seem to be in love.

15:30.760 --> 15:35.280
Weiwei waited for you by the NPC
near Jinling City gates until 8:03,

15:35.360 --> 15:37.200
and you never showed.

15:37.280 --> 15:39.600
Weiwei logged off,

15:39.680 --> 15:42.280
and she never logged back on after that.

15:42.840 --> 15:44.880
That's all I know.

15:46.840 --> 15:49.240
I see. Thank you.

15:53.160 --> 15:56.240
Why didn't you show up, Yixiao Naihe?

15:56.320 --> 15:58.600
When it was almost eight o'clock,
Weiwei told me,

15:58.680 --> 16:00.640
she believed you'd come.

16:05.560 --> 16:08.160
Sorry, I want to tell Weiwei first.

16:08.760 --> 16:12.720
Nai, I hear she was badmouthed terribly
in the public chat room that day.

16:12.800 --> 16:14.760
It's all my fault.
I'll beg for her forgiveness.

16:15.920 --> 16:20.840
Dude, why are you taking so long?
Get up...

16:21.280 --> 16:23.800
At this rate, Nai won't get any walnuts
until next year.

16:24.280 --> 16:26.360
I think,

16:26.440 --> 16:28.880
the key problem is
that she's no longer online.

16:29.160 --> 16:30.080
Say,

16:30.160 --> 16:33.000
would Mrs. Nai never log on again,
after the blow she took?

16:33.560 --> 16:36.720
If that's the case,
would Nai be single again?

16:36.800 --> 16:37.880
Why worry?

16:37.960 --> 16:40.880
If it's internet-related,
Nai will track her down.

16:40.960 --> 16:42.480
Unless she never uses the internet again.

16:43.360 --> 16:44.680
That's true.

16:45.760 --> 16:47.640
If that's the case,

16:47.880 --> 16:50.520
won't Nai have to meet her in real life?

16:51.400 --> 16:53.200
Would you do that, Nai?

16:53.960 --> 16:58.560
What are you doing?
Watching the "Girl Bandit" video?

16:59.040 --> 17:00.040
Weiwei's watching it.

17:05.920 --> 17:08.960
- You hacked into her computer?
- You found her in real life?

17:10.760 --> 17:12.000
When can I be discharged?

17:12.400 --> 17:14.680
In a few days,
when you're fully recovered.

17:15.359 --> 17:18.560
Hao Mei, put a little code
in the game for me.

17:18.920 --> 17:22.160
As soon as Weiwei logs on,
send a text to my cell automatically.

17:23.560 --> 17:25.480
Sure thing. I got it.

19:26.880 --> 19:30.280
Is it really that good?
You've watched it so many times.

20:38.280 --> 20:43.120
We watched and analyzed
"Titanic" in our last class.

20:43.360 --> 20:44.720
For this class,

20:44.800 --> 20:49.360
let's enjoy another Hollywood
classic genre film,

20:49.880 --> 20:51.120
"The Bridges of Madison County."

21:35.960 --> 21:37.000
Why are you so nice?

21:37.760 --> 21:40.640
We're classmates.
We should help each other.

21:45.640 --> 21:46.480
Thanks.

21:56.560 --> 21:57.640
Are you okay?

21:59.400 --> 22:01.640
Don't... It hurts...

22:01.720 --> 22:03.080
You two, again?

22:03.480 --> 22:05.040
I'm warning you, this is a classroom.

22:05.120 --> 22:06.960
If you want to flirt, go outside.

22:08.520 --> 22:10.240
Professor, the chair broke again.

22:10.320 --> 22:12.520
She's hurt. May I take her
to the campus doctor?

22:12.600 --> 22:13.960
Go ahead.

22:14.840 --> 22:15.720
Here.

22:43.680 --> 22:45.200
You did it on purpose, didn't you?

22:45.280 --> 22:48.000
I swear, I really didn't know
the chair was broken.

22:49.920 --> 22:53.160
Why am I always down on luck
whenever I see you?

22:53.360 --> 22:57.520
I checked my horoscope today,
and it said five stars!

22:57.800 --> 22:59.400
You ruined it all.

22:59.960 --> 23:01.640
It's my bad this time.

23:01.720 --> 23:05.640
I was my bad last time, too.
I apologize. I'm sorry.

23:08.240 --> 23:12.080
- But I was sincerely trying to help.
- Sincerely?

23:13.360 --> 23:15.080
Why did you suddenly find
your conscience?

23:16.280 --> 23:19.920
You saved me a seat
and you brought me a drink.

23:21.200 --> 23:22.280
Why are you being so nice?

23:25.320 --> 23:27.400
Tell me, honestly, what are you after?

23:29.520 --> 23:32.200
Fine, I'll get to the point.

23:33.880 --> 23:35.920
Do you know Bei Weiwei well?

23:36.520 --> 23:39.840
Weiwei? She's my roommate. Why?

23:40.960 --> 23:45.720
I got it! You're trying to bribe me,
so I'll inform you of her whereabouts,

23:46.120 --> 23:48.040
and you'll take photos
and slander her online.

23:48.840 --> 23:50.640
Why do you know about that, too?

23:50.720 --> 23:53.680
That was a misunderstanding.
I've apologized to her.

23:53.760 --> 23:58.200
Now, I find her...

23:58.720 --> 24:01.080
Now you have a crush on Weiwei?

24:03.040 --> 24:05.080
Is it that obvious?

24:06.640 --> 24:07.840
In your dreams!

24:08.480 --> 24:09.960
Ouch...

24:12.840 --> 24:13.840
I'm telling you,

24:14.280 --> 24:17.400
don't think I'd help you with Weiwei,
because you're cozying up to me.

24:17.480 --> 24:19.240
You should've done that anyway!

24:19.520 --> 24:21.120
I got hurt because of you!

24:21.760 --> 24:24.360
Fine... I'll take you to the doctor first.

24:27.440 --> 24:28.280
Open it.

24:33.000 --> 24:36.480
Thankfully my tail is okay.
Otherwise, you'd be done for!

24:36.560 --> 24:38.880
My intention was good.

24:38.960 --> 24:40.920
What happened was an accident.

24:41.400 --> 24:44.160
But, I always own up to my actions.

24:44.240 --> 24:46.360
Tell me, how can I compensate you?

24:47.160 --> 24:48.600
Applying medicine is not an option.

24:48.880 --> 24:52.920
In my nightmares!
I wouldn't let you anyway.

24:55.720 --> 24:57.120
You can treat me to yummy food.

24:57.400 --> 24:59.160
Sure! Whatever you want, we'll go now!

24:59.840 --> 25:02.160
No way! I mean three meals a day.

25:03.760 --> 25:06.240
How can I go to the cafeteria
in this state?

25:06.320 --> 25:09.440
How would I be able to fight
the crowd for food?

25:10.360 --> 25:13.200
Fine, I'll take care of
your three meals a day.

25:13.280 --> 25:16.200
I'll deliver them to your dorm every day,
until you recover.

25:16.920 --> 25:17.760
Okay.

25:29.680 --> 25:31.960
I'm surprised you kept your word.

25:32.040 --> 25:34.800
Of course! I'm a man of my word. Here.

25:36.600 --> 25:38.320
I got two, one for you.

25:38.400 --> 25:41.280
- One...
- How did you know I eat two breakfasts?

25:42.000 --> 25:44.120
You know I like a drink
for breakfast, too?

25:53.520 --> 25:58.840
You want me to give
one of the breakfasts to Weiwei, right?

26:02.200 --> 26:04.400
Don't deny it. You think I'm dumb?

26:05.640 --> 26:06.640
Well...

26:06.720 --> 26:08.440
Is Weiwei upset about something?

26:09.160 --> 26:10.000
How did you know?

26:10.440 --> 26:12.880
She seems kind of down.

26:12.960 --> 26:14.640
You're her roommate. Do you know why?

26:14.720 --> 26:16.360
Of course, I do.

26:18.320 --> 26:20.680
But why should I tell you?

26:20.760 --> 26:22.640
It concerns Weiwei's privacy.

26:23.560 --> 26:27.560
I'm telling you, don't bother bribing me
to put in a good word for you.

26:27.640 --> 26:32.760
Even though I, Zhao Erxi, am
a sucker for food and... Food...

26:33.040 --> 26:35.360
But I'd never sell out a friend.

26:36.120 --> 26:38.440
Clever! I do want to bribe you.

26:40.880 --> 26:43.200
You're admitting it?

26:43.280 --> 26:44.360
Why shouldn't I?

26:44.440 --> 26:46.440
I never tried to hide the fact
that I like her.

26:47.680 --> 26:49.840
If you won't help me, that's fine.

26:49.920 --> 26:52.320
I won't give up anyway.

26:59.840 --> 27:02.720
Master, you're upset today, aren't you?

27:02.800 --> 27:05.680
What's on your mind?
Do you want to talk?

27:08.280 --> 27:12.120
It's nothing, I just suddenly have an urge
to fall in love.

27:18.000 --> 27:22.120
But would anyone be attracted
to a girl like me?

27:26.400 --> 27:28.640
BUT WOULD ANYONE BE ATTRACTED

27:28.720 --> 27:30.240
TO A GIRL LIKE ME?

27:34.400 --> 27:38.080
Only because they don't understand you
and have misconceptions about you.

27:38.160 --> 27:40.840
I used to be one of them.

27:44.520 --> 27:47.160
Master, come on, I'll take you somewhere.

27:50.600 --> 27:52.080
Where?

27:54.960 --> 27:56.480
You'll know when we get there.

28:05.000 --> 28:08.080
- Where are you taking me?
- It's just up ahead.

28:18.560 --> 28:20.440
It's so pretty!

28:42.000 --> 28:42.840
Do you like it?

28:44.520 --> 28:45.360
Yes.

28:52.760 --> 28:53.600
There's more.

30:41.040 --> 30:45.040
What are you doing?
Why are you so romantic suddenly?

30:45.360 --> 30:50.160
Are you trying to practice this on me,
so you can pursue some girls?

30:54.520 --> 30:57.120
Master, you're a girl.

31:05.160 --> 31:08.000
Master, my level
has almost surpassed yours now.

31:08.080 --> 31:10.680
I don't think I want to be
your apprentice anymore.

31:14.200 --> 31:16.880
What? Are you going to betray your master?

31:17.280 --> 31:19.600
No way! You're being ungrateful.

31:25.680 --> 31:28.280
No, I mean, Wei...

31:32.440 --> 31:37.040
Huantian Xidi, will you be
my in-game spouse?

31:40.880 --> 31:45.600
He's confessing his love for me!

31:59.800 --> 32:02.000
Yes, I will.

32:24.560 --> 32:26.800
Now I know how I feel,

32:26.880 --> 32:28.800
I should rush to log on,

32:28.880 --> 32:31.680
and nail Naihe down
by any means necessary.

32:32.560 --> 32:34.920
After all, I'm single, and so is Naihe.

32:36.000 --> 32:40.320
But why am I afraid to log on?

32:42.040 --> 32:45.560
Oh, no... I must be overtaken by
the "Awkwardians"!

32:46.320 --> 32:52.000
Or, is this what they call "shyness"?

32:52.800 --> 32:57.160
Forget it.
I'll study for the exams first.

32:57.240 --> 33:00.680
I'll log on after the exams.
I'm sure he'll be around.

33:02.880 --> 33:03.720
Right.

33:30.440 --> 33:33.560
- Hello?
- Hi, is this Ms. Bei Weiwei?

33:34.640 --> 33:36.280
Yes. Who's this?

33:36.560 --> 33:37.880
Hello, Ms. Bei,

33:37.960 --> 33:40.560
this is Fengteng's operations division
of "A Chinese Ghost Story."

33:42.240 --> 33:43.680
Operations division
of "A Chinese Ghost Story"?

33:45.400 --> 33:47.480
May I know what this is about?

33:47.560 --> 33:49.880
First of all, congratulations
on your video

33:49.960 --> 33:53.400
being voted number one
in our Video Drama Contest.

33:53.480 --> 33:57.280
I've watched the video.
It's well-made. We all love it.

33:59.160 --> 34:01.280
- Thanks.
- Here's the thing,

34:01.360 --> 34:03.400
company executives
happened to see your video,

34:03.480 --> 34:05.840
and were inspired by the plot
of marriage by abduction.

34:05.920 --> 34:08.440
They want to add a marriage
by abduction feature into the game.

34:08.520 --> 34:11.920
They also want to use your video
for the marketing campaign.

34:12.000 --> 34:14.199
So they want to buy
the rights to your video.

34:14.280 --> 34:16.679
Would you be willing to do so?

34:19.840 --> 34:22.280
May I give you an answer later?

34:22.360 --> 34:25.239
I didn't make the video on my own.

34:25.320 --> 34:27.159
I have to consult with my friend.

34:27.520 --> 34:30.560
Sure. When will you be able
to make a decision?

34:32.159 --> 34:33.440
In two or three days.

34:33.520 --> 34:35.600
Then... May I call you on Monday?

34:36.639 --> 34:37.960
Sure.

34:38.040 --> 34:40.239
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

34:43.040 --> 34:44.760
Weiwei,

34:45.840 --> 34:48.120
you're sulking one minute
and elated the next.

34:48.199 --> 34:50.840
Can you give us a mood-shift forecast?

34:51.199 --> 34:53.159
Didn't you hear?

34:53.239 --> 34:56.679
You said something about
"A Chinese Ghost Story."

34:57.160 --> 35:00.200
Who was that?
Come on, indulge my curiosity.

35:01.280 --> 35:04.600
I made a video a while back, remember?

35:04.680 --> 35:07.440
Now Fengteng wants to buy
the rights to my video.

35:07.520 --> 35:09.840
They said it inspired them,

35:09.920 --> 35:12.040
so they want to add
a new feature to the game.

35:12.680 --> 35:14.040
Is this solid?

35:15.000 --> 35:16.520
I think so.

35:16.600 --> 35:20.120
Fengteng is pretty good with
protecting players' personal info.

35:20.440 --> 35:24.280
Aside from their staff, I don't think
anyone knows I'm Luwei Weiwei.

35:24.360 --> 35:28.560
Anyway, it doesn't do them any good
to con me into doing this, right?

35:29.520 --> 35:30.360
Good.

35:32.200 --> 35:33.520
Go do your exercise sheets.

35:33.840 --> 35:35.720
Go now... I'm going to play my game.

35:36.640 --> 35:38.320
She's herself again.

35:58.000 --> 35:59.680
Weiwei, come see me.

36:03.160 --> 36:06.520
Why am I suddenly a bit nervous?

36:10.320 --> 36:11.920
Where are you, Mrs. Nai?

36:12.480 --> 36:15.560
I'm the one at fault. I bear the rod
to ask for punishment and forgiveness.

36:16.680 --> 36:19.200
Yugong used the right idiom!

36:22.400 --> 36:25.400
Mrs. Nai, it's all my fault.
You can beat the heck out of me.

36:26.600 --> 36:27.640
What's the matter?

36:30.600 --> 36:35.640
I was driving on the way back from
the business dinner, and the car crashed.

36:41.440 --> 36:42.720
Are you okay?

36:43.120 --> 36:46.880
You're online now,
so I guess you're fine?

36:49.080 --> 36:52.200
We're fine. The truck suddenly
veered to the left without signaling.

36:52.280 --> 36:54.320
We managed to dodge the truck,

36:54.400 --> 36:56.560
but we smashed into a tree.

36:56.640 --> 36:59.240
I'm okay, because Nai pushed me
out of harm's way.

36:59.320 --> 37:02.760
Nai suffered a slight concussion,
but he woke up after just a day.

37:04.360 --> 37:07.920
What do you mean by "just a day"?
It's serious, okay?

37:08.000 --> 37:09.320
I'll go see Naihe.

37:31.920 --> 37:34.160
Why are you online?
Why aren't you resting?

37:38.280 --> 37:39.240
I'm fine now.

37:40.400 --> 37:43.040
You still shouldn't be playing.
It's very tiring.

37:44.040 --> 37:46.400
I'm not playing. I just have it on.

37:47.680 --> 37:49.200
Just have it on?

37:49.960 --> 37:52.480
Why did I receive your text,
as soon as I logged on?

37:59.120 --> 38:01.680
Does your head still hurt?

38:04.960 --> 38:07.360
I'm sorry for standing you up that day.

38:09.080 --> 38:12.080
Compared to your injuries,
that was nothing.

38:13.800 --> 38:15.720
I haven't logged on in days.

38:15.800 --> 38:17.760
Has Naihe waited for days?

38:18.400 --> 38:20.680
Does he think I'm mad at him?

38:21.160 --> 38:22.720
I'm not mad.

38:22.800 --> 38:26.880
At first, I was afraid
he wouldn't be online, and then...

38:27.440 --> 38:31.040
I have exams coming up.
That's why I didn't log on for days.

38:36.760 --> 38:37.680
I know.

38:38.840 --> 38:41.840
You know? No, you don't!

38:45.480 --> 38:48.760
By the way, Fengteng Technology
called me today.

38:48.840 --> 38:52.320
They want to buy the rights to our video.
How should I reply?

38:56.000 --> 38:57.160
That's a bit complicated.

38:58.920 --> 39:00.240
- Is it?
- Yes.

39:01.080 --> 39:02.240
So...

39:05.680 --> 39:06.560
Let's talk in person.

39:07.960 --> 39:09.360
This is my cellphone number.

39:11.960 --> 39:13.880
This is Naihe's cellphone number?

39:28.920 --> 39:31.720
My cellphone was stolen.
I haven't replaced it.

39:33.160 --> 39:36.480
It's okay. Just take down my number.

39:40.440 --> 39:42.960
Sure. Where shall we meet?

39:45.000 --> 39:47.280
I'm at Qing University.
You're in Capital City too, right?

39:49.360 --> 39:54.040
Yes, I'll pick you up on campus.
When are you free?

39:58.840 --> 40:01.360
I have an exam tomorrow.
I'll be free after 11:30.

40:03.920 --> 40:06.840
I'll wait by the university's east gate
at 12 o'clock.

40:10.800 --> 40:14.240
Let's do 11:35,
so we don't have to wait for half an hour.

40:17.720 --> 40:19.640
Why did I reveal my thoughts?

40:20.000 --> 40:23.680
I can't even wait for half an hour?
That shows how eager I am!

40:23.760 --> 40:27.640
I'll call you tomorrow.
I have to go now. Bye-bye!

40:50.440 --> 40:54.080
Weiwei... Why are you running around?
What are you looking for?

40:57.400 --> 40:58.760
Will you go shopping for clothes with me?

41:05.120 --> 41:10.680
I never thought Weiwei would want
to shop for clothes!

41:10.760 --> 41:14.800
That just goes to show
life is full of surprises.

41:15.600 --> 41:16.800
How do you like this?

41:18.360 --> 41:20.680
What do you think of the dress?

44:08.960 --> 44:11.400
Subtitle translation by Lu Yuhan
